## 9. Phase 0 detailed requirements: join, hear, speak

### Phase 0 objective

Build the smallest working version of the system where:

> The agent joins a Google Meet call and can have a spoken conversation with the people in the meeting.

### User flow

1. User opens the hosted web app.
2. User pastes a Google Meet link.
3. User clicks “Start Agent.”
4. Backend sends `JOIN_MEETING` command to the Mac worker.
5. Mac worker opens Chrome.
6. Chrome joins the Google Meet using the already-logged-in agent account.
7. Agent enters the meeting.
8. Agent audio pipeline starts.
9. Agent listens to meeting audio.
10. Agent waits until there is silence.
11. Agent speaks out loud into the meeting.

### Functional requirements

#### FR-0.1: Paste Meet link

The web app must allow the user to paste a Google Meet link.

#### FR-0.2: Send command to Mac worker

The hosted backend must send the meeting link to the connected Mac worker.

#### FR-0.3: Worker online status

The web app must show whether the Mac worker is online.

Example statuses:

```text
Worker offline
Worker connected
Joining meeting
In meeting
Listening
Speaking
Error
```

#### FR-0.4: Join Google Meet

The Mac worker must open the Meet link in Chrome and attempt to join the meeting.

For the hackathon MVP, the Chrome profile should already be logged in to the agent-only Google account.

#### FR-0.5: Use agent-only account

The agent should join as a separate participant, not as the user.

Example display name:

```text
AI Project Agent
```

#### FR-0.6: Hear meeting audio

The worker must capture the meeting audio through a virtual audio route.

#### FR-0.7: Speak into meeting

The worker must route the Gemini-generated audio into the microphone input used by Google Meet.

#### FR-0.8: Silence-based turn-taking

The agent must avoid interrupting people. It should wait for a short silence window before responding.

Suggested MVP behavior:

```text
If someone is speaking: do not respond.
If silence lasts around 800–1500 ms: response may begin.
If someone starts speaking while agent is speaking: stop or shorten response.
```

Gemini Live has voice/activity-related configuration capabilities, so the first implementation should use built-in activity detection where possible before building a custom VAD pipeline.

#### FR-0.9: Natural addressing

The agent should not require a fixed wake word.

It should respond when it believes someone is asking it for help.

Example phrases:

```text
Can you help us with this?
What do you think, agent?
Can someone summarize this?
Can you turn this into tasks?
Could you check the brief?
```

#### FR-0.10: Simple spoken personality

The agent should speak briefly and clearly.

Default style:

```text
Helpful
Concise
Meeting-friendly
Does not over-talk
Confirms what it is doing
```

Example:

```text
Sure. I’ll join the discussion and wait for a pause before responding.
```

