## 13. Phase 4 requirements: Trello task creation

### Objective

The agent turns the project brief and meeting discussion into Trello cards.

### Trello implementation

Use the Trello API to create cards, then open the Trello board in Chrome to show the result. The Trello REST API supports creating cards, which makes this more reliable than clicking through the UI during a live demo.

### Card format

Each card should include:

```text
Title
Short description
Optional checklist with 2–4 items
```

### Example cards

```text
Card 1: Implement Google Meet Join Flow
Description: Build the Mac worker command that opens Chrome and joins a pasted Google Meet link using the agent account.

Checklist:
- Receive meeting link from backend
- Open Chrome profile
- Join Meet
- Report status to web app
```

```text
Card 2: Build Voice Loop
Description: Route meeting audio to Gemini Live and send Gemini spoken output back into the meeting.

Checklist:
- Configure virtual audio
- Stream audio to Gemini Live
- Play response into Meet
- Add silence-based turn-taking
```

