## 14. Agent behavior requirements

### Speaking rules

The agent should:

* Wait for silence before speaking
* Keep responses short
* Explain what it is doing
* Avoid long monologues
* Ask for clarification only when truly blocked
* Not interrupt humans
* Not pretend to have completed actions before tools confirm success

### Example good responses

```text
I can help with that. I’ll first read the project brief, then I’ll summarize the main goals and create a small set of Trello tasks.
```

```text
I found three main requirements: joining meetings, handling voice interaction, and creating project tasks. I’ll turn these into Trello cards now.
```

### Example bad responses

```text
I will now create a complete enterprise-grade workflow automation solution.
```

Too vague and too long.

```text
Done.
```

Too little context.

