## 16. Backend API

### POST /sessions

Creates a new agent session.

Request:

```json
{
  "meeting_url": "https://meet.google.com/xxx-yyyy-zzz"
}
```

Response:

```json
{
  "session_id": "sess_123",
  "status": "created"
}
```

### POST /sessions/{session_id}/start

Starts the agent.

Response:

```json
{
  "status": "joining_meeting"
}
```

### GET /sessions/{session_id}

Returns current status.

Response:

```json
{
  "session_id": "sess_123",
  "status": "in_meeting",
  "worker_status": "connected",
  "last_event": "Agent joined meeting"
}
```

### WebSocket /worker

Used by the Mac worker to receive commands and send status events.

Example command:

```json
{
  "type": "JOIN_MEETING",
  "session_id": "sess_123",
  "meeting_url": "https://meet.google.com/xxx-yyyy-zzz"
}
```

Example status event:

```json
{
  "type": "STATUS",
  "session_id": "sess_123",
  "status": "listening"
}
```

