## 18. Audio design

### Goal

The agent must hear the meeting and speak into the meeting without relying on the physical microphone and speaker.

### Required routing

```text
Google Meet output audio
  ↓
Virtual audio input captured by worker
  ↓
Gemini Live
  ↓
Gemini output audio
  ↓
Virtual microphone input selected in Google Meet
```

### Key risks

* Echo
* Feedback loop
* Gemini hearing itself
* Wrong input/output selected in Meet
* macOS permission issues
* Browser permission prompts
* Audio latency
* Agent speaking over humans

### MVP strategy

Start with a controlled setup:

* One dedicated Mac
* One Chrome profile
* One Google Meet account
* Pre-configured audio devices
* Pre-granted browser permissions
* Same Meet testing room
* Manual verification before demo

